<subSubSection type="description">
<paragraph box="[281,1190,1332,1644]" pageId="19" pageNumber="272" type="mainText">Succulent, articulate shrubs without distinct leaves. Flowers 3 to 5 in the axil of peltate, scale-like, persistent, spirally arranged, free bracts; perianth 4-5- lobed at the apex, unmodified in fruit; stamens 1-2; stigmas 2(-3). Seeds vertical; embryo hooked; radicle inferior; perisperm abundant. Three spp., N, C and S America.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
